What are Headers?

Headers are key–value pairs sent along with HTTP requests and responses that carry metadata (extra information) about the request/response.

👉 Simple:

Body = actual data
Headers = information about data
📦 2️⃣ Types of Headers
🔹 1. Request Headers (Client → Server)

👉 Sent by browser/client

Examples:
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer token
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0
🔹 2. Response Headers (Server → Client)

👉 Sent by server

Examples:
Content-Type: text/html
Cache-Control: no-cache
Set-Cookie: user=123
